RCCS will have two indoor winter soccer teams again this year! Indoor soccer tryouts will begin Friday, September 13th. Start practicing now so you are ready!

What will you need for practice?
Shin guards
Soccer socks (must completely cover shin guards)
Proper shoes (regular sneakers or flat indoor soccer shoes)
Who can try out? Girls and boys grades 6-12
What are tryouts for? To form two RCCS teams to compete in the Lou Ramos Winter League
Where are tryouts and practices? In RCCS MS/HS gym
Where are games? Lou Ramos Center, 1344 N Sherman St, Allentown, PA 18109
When are tryouts? Fridays in September starting on the 13th
When are practices? typically on Fridays from 3:15-4:15 p.m.
When are games? typically nights or weekends

Questions? Email Ms. Marchini at cwaite@myrccs.com.

post_text:
Professional Development at Roberto Clemente Charter School.
RCCS is proud to collaborate with Lehigh University to offer quality and high level professional development to our staff. On August 21st Lehigh University's Dean, Dr. William Gaudelli offered a training on Global Citizenship. Equally important, Professor, Dr. Gina Gullo offered a training on the topic of Implicit Bias. Thank you Dr. Gaudelli and Dr. Gullo for your expertise in favor of the Roberto Clemente Charter School students and staff!

Roberto Clemente Charter School
July 19, 2019 at 10:23 AM ¬∑

Rccs Families! We want to welcome the new 6th graders families of this 2019-20 school year!! The first day of school will be Tuesday, September 3rd, 2019.

Copy and paste this. Don't share it, your status could help someone in need that doesn't want to speak up and ask for help. We all need a little help sometimes.

Teacher Appreciation Week is a weeklong celebration in the United States observed in May. RCCS would like to celebrate this week by saying thanks to our dedicated staff and recognizing their hard work. We invite parents and students to offer a word of encouragement and appreciation to our staff during the week of May 6-10.

Furthermore, RCCS will have a half school day on Friday, May 10th to recognize our staff. Please note that all students will be dismissed at 12:00 p.m. on this day. Arrangements have been made to provide transportation for bus students. The school bus will pick up students at usual time in the morning and will be at the school at 12:00 p.m. to take them home. If your child does not take the bus, we kindly ask you to make arrangements for transportation.
If you have any questions regarding the staff appreciation week or the early dismissal day, please do not hesitate to call the school at (610) 439 -5181.

post_text:
Wow! The JV soccer team dominated last night's game! They versed Saucon Valley and ended with a score of 10 to 3!!!

Make sure to congratulate Christopher Garcia and Roman Paniagua for an amazing job in goal!

Scoring one goal each were Marlon Cordova, Elvin Uruchima, Joel Fernandez, and Christopher Garcia.

Scoring two goals each were Christian Reyes, Javier Reyes and Guillermo Tavarez.

There were two MVPs for this game- Christopher Garcia for his diving saves in goal (he looked like a real pro!) and Emily Encarnacion for showing the boys how it's done on defense! She was scared to play at first, but within a couple of minutes she was in her groove. She won the ball each time she challenged another player!

Everyone did a phenomenal job!

JV will play their last regular game of the season next Thursday at 7:30 against the same team. It would be great to see both students and staff there to support our team.

What a tremendous season this has been for our first annual indoor soccer program at RCCS! Woohoo!!!

Congratulations to our newly CPR and first aid certified students! Our high school students had the opportunity to participate in a CPR and first aid training course through the American Red Cross and completed the coursework with the help of our Emergency Services club advisor, Mr. Burgermeister. Nice work, everyone!

If your child is interested in learning more about careers in the emergency services field, contact Ms. Fisher today to get them signed up for Emergency Services!

Thanks,

These items will be donated to homeless shelters in Allentown!
